<span id="freeTextContainer10834265357686018464">This novel belongs to the few ones which I reread at least twice yearly. It;s one of the best novels ever written. I&apos;ve been the admirer of The Name of the Rose for many, many years now, and I remember reading it for the first time when I was in high school. I reckon I didn&apos;t understand much then regarding the dispute which is the theme around which this novel revolves. Now, with every read, I discover something new... what could any reader expect more from a novel?</span>
  <span id="freeText10834265357686018464" style="display:none">This novel belongs to the few ones which I reread at least twice yearly. It;s one of the best novels ever written. I've been the admirer of The Name of the Rose for many, many years now, and I remember reading it for the first time when I was in high school. I reckon I didn't understand much then regarding the dispute which is the theme around which this novel revolves. Now, with every read, I discover something new... what could any reader expect more from a novel?</span>
