    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2031883395" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2031883395" />
    <a title="Steven Godin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/26706841-steven-godin"><img alt="Steven Godin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1621019440p2/26706841.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2031883395?book_show_action=true">Sep 20, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Steven Godin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Steven Godin" href="/user/show/26706841-steven-godin">Steven Godin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26706841-steven-godin?shelf=italy">italy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/26706841-steven-godin?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2031883395" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2138720064559168514">Set in a medieval Italian monastery, Eco&apos;s historical murder mystery contained a well oiled challenging plot that really does require your up most commitment, but one that seemed to never want to end. It dragged on...and...on...and...on! It went over the top with Latin quotes that had me scratching my head, and lengthy, repetitive passages that just had me crying out &quot;Eco!, please just cut to the chase!&quot; I won&apos;t bother to go into the fine details, all I will say it that I read this over about th</span>
  <span id="freeText2138720064559168514" style="display:none">Set in a medieval Italian monastery, Eco's historical murder mystery contained a well oiled challenging plot that really does require your up most commitment, but one that seemed to never want to end. It dragged on...and...on...and...on! It went over the top with Latin quotes that had me scratching my head, and lengthy, repetitive passages that just had me crying out "Eco!, please just cut to the chase!" I won't bother to go into the fine details, all I will say it that I read this over about three months, when it would have benefited reading in bigger chunks over a shorter period of time, but the reason for this was it simply never held my attention for long enough. There were moments when I just felt like throwing in the towel, but somehow persevered, and by it's finale I kind of just went "Hmm" and within a day it was almost forgotten. It's a shame, as I so wanted to love this.<br />But all in all, it was flawed, and too darn long.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2138720064559168514" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


